{"key":"processedPost-19573590","value":{"id":19573590,"first":19571917,"last":19577098,"when":1392557659,"utime":"02/16/14 03:34 PM","content":"<blockquote>Quote:<br /><b>Dreamchild said:</b><br /><br />I read that you're supposed to take the aborts out as soon as you spot them so the cake/bulk sub doesn't waste energy on them. Also I believe they'll rot which isn't good so I pick them as I see them.<br /></blockquote><br /><br />Cutting at the base is correct when harvesting, but aborts don't rot nor do they use or waste energy.<br /><br />Ripping large chunks of substrate when one harvests is just dumb because new pins won't form in the divot.&nbsp; Thus, you ruin that part of your fruiting surface for future flushes.&nbsp; It isn't primarily about contamination, although molds sometimes do colonize the damaged substrate.<br /><br />Mushroom stumps do not rot.<br />RR","title":"Re: Okay so when who harvesting who pulls and who cuts?","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}